        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=8740&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=About+pet+hit+points%2E%2E%2Esorry+Potus"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Long before we get those hit point increases for our pets, we should get the following things:</P><P>1).  Death Peace (FD upgrade that SK's get and we *don't*<BR>2).  A change of reagent for Infusion and Trucidation<BR>3).  A change of the Undead Mez skill from Luclin to either a). allow it to be used more often, or b).  Make it a spell not a skill, or c). see #4<BR>4).  An upgrade to Screaming Terror<BR>5).  An upgrade to our pet heal spell line (and no, I don't count the new skill that takes way too much effort to get so that I can LoH my pet once an hour)<BR>6).  An upgrade to our AE line so that we can have some fun with the AE groups for a change.<BR>7).  A new epic graphic<BR>8).  Boosted epic stats<BR>9).  A post-50 upgrade to Shackle line<BR>10).  Fix QVoZ so that it works when Lich'd<BR>11).  An upgrade to Torbin's Acid Blast<BR>12).  Change Levant back to it's previous, non-zoneloading state<BR>13).  Make the Flesh to Bone skill a necro discipline for 51st level or so.<BR>14).  Give us group DMF<BR>15).  Make our pets look better since SoL release<BR>16).  Upgrade spectre model and allow it to be armed with 2 weapons if we choose to do so (for proc effects)<BR>17).  Give us somewhere to raise Venril Sathir faction (other than killing Severilous) - evils in general got fuxxed in Kunark.<BR>18).  Why do half the skeleton mobs in Luclin register as non-undead?<BR>19).  Group Banshee Aura maybe?  or at *least* a pet targetable Aura<BR>20).  Make our Luclin spells work.</P><P>All I can think of off the top of my head.  Feel free to add some.  Bottom line is, hundreds of necros across all the servers have achieved 60th with the use of the 53, 56, and 59 pets.  The pets are reliable when used properly.  There are far greater fish to fry when it comes to necromancers' abilities.</font></td>
      </tr>

