			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=1833')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_messengers.asp?mode=ICQ&ICQ=33510874&M_NAME=Nyxx')"><img src="http://online.mirabilis.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=33510874&img=5" height=15 width=15 alt="Send Nyxx an ICQ Message" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=70417&TOPIC_ID=8740&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=About+pet+hit+points%2E%2E%2Esorry+Potus&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I don't believe you people! READ WHAT YOU ARE TYPING.</P><P>1) Why should we get this? Just because we are the parent class to shadowknights doesn't mean we should have every spell they have *think of rangers and druids!*<BR>2) I agree with this.<BR>3) We are not enchanters of the undead, we are supposed to be damage dealers.<BR>4) I agree with this.<BR>5) Shadowbond + Pact of Shadow, learn to use them well my friend.<BR>6) Our AoEs are point blank, do you really want to be standing next to the mob casting a high damage spell on it? No.<BR>7) I like the current graphic.<BR>8) Um no, not neccessary.<BR>9) Maybe, but I dont think we NEED it.<BR>10) I agree with this.<BR>11) Maybe, but I dont think we NEED it.<BR>12) This is a self-only succor spell, its like this to clear aggro. Should stay as it is.<BR>13) I agree with this.<BR>14) Er we already have Group DMF.<BR>15) They look fine.<BR>16) I agree with this.<BR>17) I'm just going to laugh at you for this one.<BR>18) Same thing goes with the plants, why doesnt Defoliation work on them? Oh, right they are "magic".<BR>19) Maybe, but I dont think we NEED this.<BR>20) They should have been working since it was released.</P><P></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
