        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I do agree with most of what the initial poster wrote.  There are a couple that I don't care about.  Believe me, I do read what was written and thoroughly understand it.</P><P>The graphic and stats on the epic are pathetic.  If you use it in my guild for any type of event you will be told to stop.  So, you are 60 and you can now use your epic in an exp group.  Great.  Just what you needed.  The look of the duck stick is pathetic and humiliating.  No two ways about it.</P><P>Again, in our guild you don't use pets.  If you are in an experience group you may but on Events where we fight you don't.  Well, maybe on a couple large mobs like Vindi, Dain, and the Statue.</P><P>Necros are the master of the dead, not SKs.  Necros should have received an upgraded FD.  It doesn't even fit eq history nor roleplaying to have SKs exceed the necro at being able to Feign Death.  What it does is put the SK in a competing role with the monk for pulling in the high end game.  Giving Necros an improved FD doesn't mean they would take any portion of the pull duties away from the monk.</P><P>Most players do play their pets well.  Heck, it is sort of difficult to screw up.  You'd have to be a compelete nincompoop to screw up with pets these days.  The pets need enhancements.  Imagine when they gave all pets the ability to dual wield/double attack automatically at a certain level.  This took away the unique advantage of the 59 pet.  What'd they do?  Made the pets able to hit slightly higher level mobs better and made them fearless.  So, what do you get on big mobs?  Players that may be feared away and pets that can continue to fight but get whacked because they hit slighly harder and they are closest to the mobs.</P><P>I think many things need to be adjusted.  Verant is a simple minded group of people that don't review the impact of their changes.  I remember teaching programming classes and letting students know that when they make some changes they have to review their code for possible breakage.  Well, most didn't, they just continued on and when the code was tested it broke.  Same type of logic applies to classes in EQ.  You stretch things too far for some classes and nerf others you'd better be willing to review what you did and adjust or you will possibly have broken something.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
