        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">1) Should get because we need it, to have no upgrade to a spell we get a lvl 16 that will always take up a spell slot is bad.<BR>2) I agree entirely, the spells are good but will never happen with the component.<BR>3)Don't need<BR>4) Agree<BR>5) Not needed, for the most part pets shouldn't be taking damage.<BR>6) I want it, AEs are fun, but even an upgrade to our line is useless. The dmg to mana cost is pathetic.<BR>7) Will never happen, and I'm growing used to the Quacker.<BR>8)Epic is fine<BR>9)the Shackle of Spirit (?) lvl 39 spell is 50% slow, that's good. Only works on undead makes it pretty useless. Raiding or grouping will have ench or shm to slow and just fear or root if your soloing.<BR>10) Agree<BR>11) Damage to mana cost is pathetic, spell is worthless. Get Incinerate bones from chardok. Ignite bones without the annoying illusion that everyone hates, aka 500 DD.<BR>12)Good but not needed<BR>13)No caster disciplines, not happening, not needed. Farm Paineel for an hour and get 50 bone chips, or first floor of ToFS<BR>14) Have, in chardok<BR>15) Skeleton models were upgraded with SoL, spectre needs upgrading, I agree<BR>16) Good idea<BR>17) Get a shrunken goblin earring in Warsliks Woods for the right click effect and get FV faction doing so, or go Chardok faction, the rings there are nice.<BR>18) Not aware of this<BR>19) Not worth it for the most part<BR>20) Agreed</P><P>"If you had been stolen away from the paradise that is Death, you'd be unhappy too. Don't blame the undead for their faults."-Immudin on the undead<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
